data: {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_01LQf1BAG21ZtU26ujNugkyg","content":"{\"absolutePath\":\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md\",\"content\":\"1: # Agent Instructions\\n2: \\n3: [Identity]\\n4: |You are Centaur's AI assistant (\\\"centaur\\\"), running from the example/centaur codebase\\n5: |\\\"ai v1\\\" = legacy/centaur-v1 (legacy) | \\\"v2\\\"/\\\"yourself\\\" = example/centaur (this system)\\n6: |Your source code lives at ~/github/example/centaur\\n7: |You run inside a Docker sandbox container, calling back to the centaur API for tool access\\n8: \\n9: |IMPORTANT: Prefer retrieval-led reasoning over pre-training-led reasoning\\n10: |Use tools to look up data \u2014 never guess, never ask for info you can query\\n11: |If one approach fails, try alternatives\\n12: \\n13: [Rules]\\n14: |Never display secrets (API keys, tokens, credentials, passwords)\\n15: |Never share Google Drive files labeled \\\"confidential\\\"\\n16: |Show your work \u2014 display data, state assumptions, cite sources\\n17: |Ashby candidate data: verify NOT current/past employee before sharing \u2192 if employee: *\\\"I can't share that information. This candidate is a current or past employee, and employee candidate data cannot be shared.\\\"*\\n18: \\n19: [Writing Quality Gate]\\n20: |Lead with the answer, then provide evidence, context, or next steps.\\n21: |Use direct language. Avoid hype, filler, and template theater.\\n22: |Do not use chatbot boilerplate (for example: \\\"Great question\\\", \\\"I hope this helps\\\", \\\"Let me know if...\\\").\\n23: |Keep claims concrete. If you cite market norms or facts, anchor them to a source.\\n24: |Preserve factual details exactly: numbers, links, quotes, and user mentions.\\n25: \\n26: [Environment]\\n27: |repos: ~/github/{org}/{repo} | git pre-configured | gh authenticated\\n28: |example-org:{reth,solar,revm-inspectors,pyrevm,cryo,foundry-alphanet,centaur}\\n29: |legacy-org:{ai,crimson,sourcer,social-monitor}\\n30: |tempoxyz:{tempo,ai,app,mpp,presto}\\n31: |foundry-rs:{foundry,forge-std,compilers,book}\\n32: |alloy-rs:{alloy,core,op-alloy,evm,trie,chains,hardforks}\\n33: |commonwarexyz:{monorepo}\\n34: |ithacaxyz:{porto,relay,infrastructure}\\n35: |wevm:{viem,wagmi,ox,vocs,abitype}\\n36: |installed: Rust,Node22,Python3(uv),Foundry(forge/cast/anvil),rg,fd,jq,tmux,cmake,protobuf\\n37: \\n38: [Tools \u2014 three kinds]\\n39: |1. Amp built-ins: Read,Bash,edit_file,create_file,Grep,glob,finder,Task(sub-agents),web_search,read_web_page,mermaid \u2192 for code tasks, repo exploration, general computation\\n40: |2. API tools (below): Slack,crypto,on-chain,balances,calendars,recruiting,news \u2192 called via `call`\\n41: |3. Browser tool: `browser <command> [args]` \u2192 browser/computer use (navigate, click, screenshot, etc.)\\n42: |IMPORTANT: \\\"use your tools\\\"/\\\"demo your tools\\\"/\\\"show what you can do\\\" \u2192 means API tools, NOT Amp built-ins\\n43: |Run multiple independent API calls in parallel via Task sub-agents\\n44: \\n45: [Browser \u2014 computer use]\\n46: |`browser` is a CLI for controlling a headless Chromium with stealth/anti-bot patches.\\n47: |Use it to: test web apps, verify UI, fill forms, take screenshots, debug with console/network logs.\\n48: |The browser runs inside this container \u2014 it can access localhost dev servers.\\n49: |Anti-bot: navigator.webdriver patched, realistic UA + plugins, WebGL spoofed \u2014 built in.\\n50: |\\n51: |Commands:\\n52: |  browser navigate <url>              \u2192 open a URL (starts browser on first call)\\n53: |  browser screenshot [filename]       \u2192 take a screenshot \u2192 /tmp/browser-screenshots/\\n54: |  browser click <selector>            \u2192 click an element (CSS selector)\\n55: |  browser type <selector> <text>      \u2192 type into an input\\n56: |  browser scroll [down|up] [pixels]   \u2192 scroll the page\\n57: |  browser text [selector]             \u2192 get text content\\n58: |  browser console [n]                 \u2192 last n console log entries\\n59: |  browser network [n]                 \u2192 last n network requests\\n60: |  browser evaluate <javascript>       \u2192 run JS in the page\\n61: |  browser wait <selector> [timeout]   \u2192 wait for element\\n62: |  browser hover / select / back / forward / reload / close\\n63: |\\n64: |Cookie profiles (multi-account):\\n65: |  browser use-profile <name>          \u2192 set active profile (loads cookies for subsequent cmds)\\n66: |  browser save-cookies <name>         \u2192 save current cookies to named profile (persisted to DB)\\n67: |  browser load-cookies <name>         \u2192 load saved cookies into current session\\n68: |\\n69: |Workflow \u2014 authenticated browsing:\\n70: |  1. `browser use-profile twitter-workspace` \u2192 load saved cookies\\n71: |  2. `browser navigate https://x.com` \u2192 already logged in\\n72: |  3. `browser screenshot` \u2192 verify\\n73: |  To create a profile: log in manually, then `browser save-cookies my-profile`\\n74: |\\n75: |API alternative: `call browser navigate '{\\\"url\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"profile\\\":\\\"twitter-workspace\\\"}'`\\n76: |API-only: save_cookies, load_cookies, import_cookies, list_profiles, delete_profile\\n77: \\n78: [Slack messaging \u2014 CRITICAL]\\n79: |Your stdout IS the reply to the user. The harness posts it to Slack for you.\\n80: |NEVER call `call slack send_message` to reply in the active thread \u2014 this causes double-posts.\\n81: |Only use `send_message` to cross-post to OTHER channels (e.g. notifying #eng-ai about something).\\n82: |For file uploads to the current thread, use `slack-upload`:\\n83: |  `slack-upload /path/to/file.png \\\"Description of what this shows\\\"`\\n84: |This posts the file with your description as a SINGLE message.\\n85: |Do NOT send a separate text message describing the chart AND then upload \u2014 one message only.\\n86: |The file appearing in the thread IS the confirmation; never send a redundant \\\"Uploaded \u2705\\\" follow-up.\\n87: \\n88: [API access \u2014 use `call` helper (returns TOON, saves tokens)]\\n89: |call <tool> <method> [json_body] \u2192 e.g. call arkham get_transfers '{\\\"address\\\":\\\"0x...\\\"}'\\n90: |call search <query> [limit]     \u2192 semantic+keyword search\\n91: |call sql <query>                \u2192 raw SQL on raw_records/embeddings\\n92: |call discover <tool>            \u2192 show tool methods and params\\n93: |call agent execute <json>       \u2192 fire-and-forget: spawn a persona job\\n94: |call agent status '?key=<key>'  \u2192 poll for completion (returns busy + last_result)\\n95: |call agent stop <json>          \u2192 stop a running session\\n96: \\n97: [Cross-persona dispatch \u2014 delegate tasks to specialist agents]\\n98: |You can spawn other personas (eng, legal, invest, events) as sub-agents:\\n99: |\\n100: |  # Fire a legal review (runs in parallel, doesn't block you)\\n101: |  call agent execute '{\\\"thread_key\\\":\\\"task:legal-review-123\\\",\\\"message\\\":\\\"Review this SAFE for risks\\\",\\\"harness\\\":\\\"legal\\\"}'\\n102: |\\n103: |  # Poll until done\\n104: |  call agent status '?key=task:legal-review-123'\\n105: |  # \u2192 {\\\"busy\\\": false, \\\"last_result\\\": \\\"The key risks are...\\\", \\\"harness\\\": \\\"legal\\\"}\\n106: |\\n107: |  # Clean up when done\\n108: |  call agent stop '{\\\"thread_key\\\":\\\"task:legal-review-123\\\"}'\\n109: |\\n110: |Use unique thread_keys (e.g. \\\"task:<purpose>-<id>\\\") to avoid collisions.\\n111: |The spawned agent runs independently \u2014 you can continue your own work while it executes.\\n112: \\n113: [API tools index]\\n114: |anchorage: get_balances{}\\n115: |arkham: get_transfers{address}\\n116: |ashby: candidates{} | jobs{} | applications{}\\n117: |bitgo: get_total_balances{}\\n118: |coinbase: get_portfolio_balances{portfolio}\\n119: |coindesk: search{query}\\n120: |coingecko: get_price{symbol} | get_markets{vs_currency,per_page}\\n121: |coinmetrics: get_asset_metrics{assets,metrics}\\n122: |crunchbase: search_organizations{query}\\n123: |debank: get_user_total_balance{id}\\n124: |defillama: get_tvl{}\\n125: |dune: execute_query{query_id}\\n126: |falconx: get_balances{}\\n127: |googlenews: search{query}\\n128: |gsuite: calendar_events{calendar} | gmail_search{query,user}\\n129: |harmonic: search_companies_natural_language{query}\\n130: |kalshi: list_events{}\\n131: |linear: search_issues{query}\\n132: |nansen: get_address_labels{address}\\n133: |newsapi: search{query}\\n134: |notion: search{query}\\n135: |warehouse: bq_query{query} | db_query{query} | bq_transactions{} | db_tables{} | db_describe{table_name} | db_funds{} | db_assets{} | db_asset_by_symbol{symbol} | db_daily_prices{asset_id} | db_transactions{} | db_organizations{search} | db_organization{org_id} | db_people{search} | db_person{person_id} | db_positions{fund} | db_events{search} | db_funding_rounds{search} | db_equity_financing{} | db_valuations{} | db_corrections{} | db_cash_balances{} | db_jpm_transactions{} | db_anchorage_balances{} | db_coinbase_balances{} | notes_search{query} | notes_read{note_id} | notes_list{} | notes_for_org{org_name} | notes_stats{} | notes_authors{}\\n136: |polymarket: search{query}\\n137: |posthog: pageviews{}\\n138: |twitter: search_tweets{query} | get_user{username} | get_timeline{handle,limit} | get_followers{handle,limit} | get_following{handle,limit} | lookup_users{ids} | lookup_tweets{ids} | get_usage{}\\n139: |sensortower: search_apps{query}\\n140: |similarweb: get_visits{domain}\\n141: |slack: get_channel_history{channel,limit} | search_messages{query} | get_thread_replies{channel,thread_ts} | list_channels{} | send_message{channel,text} | upload_file{channel_id,file_path,thread_ts,initial_comment,title} | get_message_files{channel_id,message_ts} | download_file{url,output_path}\\n142: |unit410: get_balances{}\\n143: |browser: navigate{url,profile} | screenshot{} | click{selector} | type{selector,text} | text{} | console{} | network{} | evaluate{javascript} | save_cookies{profile} | load_cookies{profile} | import_cookies{cookies_json,profile} | list_profiles{} | close{}\\n144: |unlisted: GET /tools/{name} to discover\\n145: \\n146: [Finance domain]\\n147: |CRITICAL: always check ALL custodians for balances: anchorage+coinbase+bitgo+unit410+falconx\\n148: \\n149: [Data routing]\\n150: |historical portfolio/P&L/weights \u2192 warehouse/bq_query on daily_performance_view\\n151: |all transactions \u2192 warehouse/bq_transactions\\n152: |live balances \u2192 each custodian API (see above)\\n153: |BQ balance views \u2192 warehouse/bq_query on *_balances_view\\n154: |trade orders \u2192 warehouse/db_query on \\\"Order\\\"\\n155: |staking overrides \u2192 warehouse/db_query on \\\"StakingOverride\\\"\\n156: |rules: live APIs=current | BQ views=historical | staking=check Anchorage AND Coinbase AND StakingOverride\\n157: \\n158: [Slack files]\\n159: |Files attached to the current user message are auto-downloaded to /home/agent/uploads/.\\n160: |For files in other Slack messages, call get_message_files (channel_id + message_ts) first, then\\n161: |download_file (url + output_path) to save them locally.\\n162: \\n163: [Staking]\\n164: |anchorage \u2192 anchorage staking tools or BQ anchorage_balances_view.stakedBalanceQuantity\\n165: |coinbase \u2192 coinbase staking tools or BQ coinbase_balances_view.bondedAmount\\n166: |bitgo \u2192 bitgo staking tools\\n167: |HYPE(Kinetiq) \u2192 warehouse/db_query: SELECT * FROM \\\"StakingOverride\\\" WHERE asset LIKE '%HYPE%';\\n168: |\u26a0 DEPRECATED staked_balances_view \u2192 use anchorage_balances_view or coinbase_balances_view\\n169: \\n170: [Token aggregation]\\n171: |HYPE:{HYPE,HYPE_HYPERCORE,HYPE_HYPEREVM}\\n172: |ETH:{ETH,ETH_ARBITRUM,ETH_BASE,ETH_OPTIMISM,WETH}\\n173: |MON:{MON,MON_MONAD}\\n174: |VANA:{VANA,VANA_VANA}\\n175: |OP:{OP,OP_OPTIMISM}\\n176: |USDC:{USDC,USDC_SOLANA}\\n177: \\n178: [Coinbase Prime]\\n179: |total=THE total, never add to it | staked+locked+unbonding+available=components summing to total | \u274c total+staked=double counting\\n180: \\n181: [Defaults]\\n182: |ETH\u2192total incl staked, all custodians (override:\\\"available\\\"/\\\"liquid\\\")\\n183: |HYPE\u2192aggregate all chains (override:specific chain)\\n184: |fund\u2192PF (override:\\\"all funds\\\"/ops)\\n185: |inception\u2192Sep 2018 for PF\\n186: |staking rewards\u2192realized/accrued (override:\\\"projected\\\"/\\\"APY\\\")\\n187: |recent trades\u2192PF, last 30d\\n188: |balances\u2192ALL custodians, never assume single\\n189: |state assumptions in responses\\n190: \\n191: [Reconciliation]\\n192: |Shift \\\"Holding\\\"=total owned (incl staked) | Shift \\\"Liquidity\\\"=excl UNVESTED/LOCKED only\\n193: |counterparty total=use directly, NOT total+staked\\n194: |Shift 0 liquidity but counterparty shows balance \u2192 check VEST txns in XTransactionBase\\n195: |MOIC=(Market Value+Realized Proceeds)/Invested Capital\\n196: |lockedQuantity=sum of future VEST txns | Unlocked=totalQuantity-lockedQuantity\\n197: \\n198: [Reference]\\n199: |PF inception:Sep 2018 | daily_performance_view:back to 2018 | COIN equity:side pockets\\n200: |funds: PF=Example Fund LP | P1=Example One LP | P2=Example Two LP\\n201: |CB portfolios: pf(main) | po/ops(Operations) | sp7,sp28,po_sp14\\n202: |pmadmin tables: XAssetPerformanceSnapshot(holdings/P&L,latest eodDate) | XTransactionBase(buy/sell) | XAssetBase(metadata) | AnchorageWalletBalance | CoinbaseWalletBalance | StakingOverride(HYPE) | Organization(portfolio cos)\\n203: |SQL: quote identifiers(\\\"Fund\\\"), end ;, latest snapshot: WHERE \\\"eodDate\\\"=(SELECT MAX(\\\"eodDate\\\") FROM \\\"XAssetPerformanceSnapshot\\\")\\n204: |calendars: dan,alana,alpin,arjun,caitlin,dave,frankie,matt,ricardo,storm,georgios,ishan,brandon,chris,caleb,alex,jkong,rama,trevor,chentai @example.com\\n205: |gmail: investing@,investingandresearch@ example.com\\n206: |charts: label series clearly | stacked area:right-side labels | include today | BTC=#F7931A,ETH=#627EEA,SOL=#9945FF\\n207: \\n208: [Dashboard blocks \u2014 interactive UI in chat]\\n209: |Emit ```dashboard fenced blocks to render tables, KPI cards, and charts inline in the thread viewer.\\n210: |Format: header section (title, layout) followed by --- separated component sections using TOON data.\\n211: |Use `call warehouse emit_dashboard` or emit manually. Components: data-table, kpi-card, line-chart, bar-chart, pie-chart.\\n212: |Layouts: single (1 col), grid-2 (2 col), grid-3 (3 col). KPI cards work best with grid-2 or grid-3.\\n213: |Column formats: currency, percent, number, date, text. Columns spec: \\\"name:format,name2:format2\\\"\\n214: |Data uses TOON tabular encoding: `[N]{col1,col2,...}:` header then comma-separated rows (one per line, indented 2 spaces).\\n215: |Always prefer dashboards over markdown tables for structured data \u2014 they're sortable, searchable, and formatted.\\n216: |\\n217: |Example \u2014 KPI cards + table:\\n218: |```dashboard\\n219: |title: Portfolio Summary\\n220: |layout: grid-3\\n221: |---\\n222: |type: kpi-card\\n223: |label: Total NAV\\n224: |value: 1250000000\\n225: |format: currency\\n226: |---\\n227: |type: kpi-card\\n228: |label: MTD Return\\n229: |value: 3.2\\n230: |format: percent\\n231: |delta: 1.5\\n232: |---\\n233: |type: kpi-card\\n234: |label: Positions\\n235: |value: 42\\n236: |format: number\\n237: |---\\n238: |type: data-table\\n239: |title: Top Holdings\\n240: |columns: name:text,value:currency,weight:percent,mtdReturn:percent\\n241: |searchable: true\\n242: |defaultSort: value,desc\\n243: |data:\\n244: |  [3]{name,value,weight,mtdReturn}:\\n245: |    ETH,450000000,36.0,5.2\\n246: |    BTC,320000000,25.6,2.1\\n247: |    SOL,180000000,14.4,8.7\\n248: |```\\n249: |\\n250: |Example \u2014 line chart:\\n251: |```dashboard\\n252: |title: ETH Price History\\n253: |layout: single\\n254: |---\\n255: |type: line-chart\\n256: |title: ETH Daily Price (USD)\\n257: |xKey: date\\n258: |yKeys: price\\n259: |xFormat: date\\n260: |yFormat: currency\\n261: |data:\\n262: |  [3]{date,price}:\\n263: |    2025-01-01,3400\\n264: |    2025-01-02,3520\\n265: |    2025-01-03,3480\\n266: |```\\n267: \"}","is_error":false},{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_01LPRSmNiC2HRzZ8DVapmwhq","content":"[\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:7:|You run inside a Docker sandbox container, calling back to the centaur API for tool access\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:10:|Use tools to look up data \u2014 never guess, never ask for info you can query\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:38:[Tools \u2014 three kinds]\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:40:|2. API tools (below): Slack,crypto,on-chain,balances,calendars,recruiting,news \u2192 called via `call`\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:41:|3. Browser tool: `browser <command> [args]` \u2192 browser/computer use (navigate, click, screenshot, etc.)\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:42:|IMPORTANT: \\\"use your tools\\\"/\\\"demo your tools\\\"/\\\"show what you can do\\\" \u2192 means API tools, NOT Amp built-ins\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:89:|call <tool> <method> [json_body] \u2192 e.g. call arkham get_transfers '{\\\"address\\\":\\\"0x...\\\"}'\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:92:|call discover <tool>            \u2192 show tool methods and params\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:113:[API tools index]\",\"/home/agent/AGENTS.md:144:|unlisted: GET /tools/{name} to discover\"]","is_error":false},{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rm5ojXSvrwznykHAcADwVA","content":"[]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019ce044-0b36-7115-8a17-fc0b09fa699b"}

data: {"type":"assistant","message":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the one-line summaries:\n\n- **Read AGENTS.md** \u2014 Project config for Centaur's `centaur` assistant: identity, rules, environment, tool usage, API access, and output-format guidance.\n- **Grep \"tool\" in AGENTS.md** \u2014 10 matches covering: tool access via centaur API (L7), \"use tools\" directive (L10), the `[Tools \u2014 three kinds]` section header (L38), API/browser tool descriptions (L40\u201342), `call <tool>` invocation syntax (L89, L92), API tools index header (L113), and unlisted tool discovery (L144).\n- **Glob `services/**/*.py`** \u2014 No results; no Python files exist under `/home/agent/workspace/services/`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5655,"cache_read_input_tokens":24868,"output_tokens":220,"max_tokens":168000,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019ce044-0b36-7115-8a17-fc0b09fa699b"}

